docs/modern-human-condition.md:93:Grief is not a flaw in attention. It is the cost of love, attachment, memory, and mortality. Practices here must not rush meaning or force peace.
docs/modern-human-condition.md:118:It is a targeted remedy for people whose self-worth rises and falls with performance, praise, correction, usefulness, or failure. It may fit perfectionistic students, achievement-driven professionals, founders, caregivers, leaders, artists, and people who turn responsibility into identity.
