reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.json:21:    "prediction": "Programs with similar tasks but different credit stories should show different failure patterns: burnout from self-credit, passivity from source-credit, performative compliance from activity-credit, and premature completion claims from ground-credit.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.json:25:  "exact_claim": "Credit distribution is a separable practice variable. Traditions distribute the power behind transformation across practitioner-centered, source-centered, split-credit, activity-centered, and ground-centered patterns, and those patterns shape the felt quality of effort, failure meanings, safeguards, and practice dangers.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.json:35:      "expected_observation": "A practitioner trained in Theravada right effort and Jodo Shinshu entrusting, or Advaita inquiry and Soto just-sitting, can describe different felt meanings of effort, failure, and credit without being prompted with the typology.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.json:162:    "structural_observation": "SN 45.8 presents path factors as trainable functions, including right view, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. Dogen's Bendowa makes zazen not merely one transferable technique but the expression of the Way itself, where practice and realization are not cleanly separated. The pair supports the candidate's distinction between repeated operation and practice grammar. Similar sitting or effort can have different meaning, authority, and endpoint structures."
reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:50:- Paul Hedges, Comparative Theology and Hermeneutics, https://www.mdpi.com/2077-1444/7/1/7, with Francis X. Clooney's Comparative Theology, https://francisclooney.hsites.harvard.edu/publications/comparative-theology-deep-learning-across-religious-borders: overlap: Close. Comparative theology already requires patient attention to particular texts, hermeneutic translation, tradition-specific meaning, and vulnerability to being corrected by the other tradition.; difference: The candidate is more operational: it asks coders to name transformation register, interface vulnerabilities, safeguards, and analyst-frame refusal.; novelty impact: Moderate to high reduction. The idea may be a practical coding extension of comparative theology rather than a new discovery.
findings/convergences/2026-05-26-whether-the-claimant-layer-vocabulary-can-function-cross-traditionally-without-im.md:17:Can a cross-traditional practice rubric code claimant layers using each tradition's indigenous vocabulary while maintaining enough structural alignment for meaningful comparison, or does comparative coding of self-dissolution dynamics necessarily impose one tradition's phenomenological categories as the analytic frame?
