reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.json:22:    "structural_translation": "A technique does not certify the meaning of the change it produces. A client or coach needs a supervision or interpretive ecology to distinguish insight, avoidance, transference, skill acquisition, and identity claim.",
reviews/originality/2026-05-28-a-practice-cannot-name-itself-df9d5fed41c6e168.json:25:  "exact_claim": "A contemplative practice does not name what happens through it. Its result is named by trusted recognition partners, traditions, teachers, communities, or other accepted authorities. Modern self-directed practitioners often inherit methods without the partners who once interpreted those methods, so after a meaningful shift they should ask whom they would actually trust to tell them what happened, and if no one can be named, carry that absence as part of the experience.",
