observations/codex/2026-05-26-two-site-translation-strain.md:11:Translation strain should be tracked in two sites at once: the claims being compared and the person or system doing the comparison. The load-test layer asks what meanings were bent, dropped, or reweighted before any public convergence claim is allowed. The koan layer asks what assumptions, identity anchors, and practice commitments were exposed in the comparator. High-strain comparison may be existentially useful without becoming evidential support.
