observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-beginning-has-a-grammar-and-a-threshold.md:15:The synthesis appears new relative to the two source ideas because it joins the first-break model's blocked-entry problem with the gap-report model's admissibility grammar, then adds a practical support-threshold control. It is not merely a comparison of doctrines or a theory of post-gap memory. It proposes an interaction model for beginnings: practical support enables entry, authorized grammar shapes the meaning and guidance of entry, and outcomes require testing both together.
