reviews/originality/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain-63091c8c41cd9e28.json:24:  "exact_claim": "A tradition's account of how transformation begins should be treated as a threshold grammar under translation strain. The research unit is the paired record of how the tradition narrates entry, what that narration predicts about threshold safeguards and beginner warnings, and what meanings are lost when entry grammars are compared across traditions. The model becomes serious only if first-break type improves prediction after anthropology, authority, conversion process, ritual inheritance, and practice ecology are coded separately.",
