./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-vector-capacity-ledger.md:7:Status: draft
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-protected-variable-after-silence.md:7:Status: draft
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-distributed-continuity-architecture.md:11:A self-dissolving or self-transcending path does not merely require a minimum self. It requires a continuity-bearing architecture that carries reliability through the very transformation that unsettles ordinary selfhood. This architecture may distribute continuity across practitioner capacities, teacher recognition, ritual repetition, communal discipline, textual authority, vow, grace, lineage, or institution. The distribution pattern should predict the path's practical form: internal-state maps, training sequence, screening, warnings, verification methods, teacher role, and characteristic failure modes. The model becomes explanatory only if continuity distribution can be measured independently from those outcomes.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-distributed-continuity-architecture.md:29:The synthesis may be an elegant taxonomy rather than an explanatory theory. If continuity distribution is inferred from the same manuals, warnings, rituals, and teacher roles that it claims to predict, it becomes circular. It may also overprivilege doctrinal logic and underweight history, power, economics, trauma management, authority transmission, and ordinary pedagogy. Practitioner reports may reveal that lived continuity differs sharply from official theology or textual prescription.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-distributed-continuity-architecture.md:57:- Add controls for institutional age, monastic or lay setting, ritual density, geography, textual versus oral transmission, teacher authority, and known risk-management concerns.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:7:Status: draft
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:11:After de-identification, traditions face a practical question: if the ordinary self is no longer trusted as owner, what holds action, care, and meaning together? The answer is a custody policy. Advaita gives custody to unobjectifiable knowing, early Buddhism refuses custody and lets dependent functioning remain ownerless, Zhuangzi gives custody to empty responsiveness, Dogen gives it to the complete present act, Ibn Arabi gives it to divine self-disclosure, and Plotinus gives it to return toward the One. This variable may explain why similar self-emptying practices yield different ethics and metaphysics without treating their resemblance as proof of one hidden reality.
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-custody-policy-after-self-release.md:24:- Additional source cards: Dogen's Uji, Zhuangzi Inner Chapters, Ibn Arabi's Fusus al-Hikam, Plotinus Enneads, and Friston FEP for empirical-adjacent boundary language.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold.md:11:When contemplative practice weakens ordinary self-ownership of attention and authority, two candidate variables shape what follows: the boundary operation and the custody rule. Boundary operation asks whether the method validates itself, undermines itself, or becomes irrelevant as the practitioner matures beyond method-talk. Custody rule asks where freed attention and authority may belong afterward: no owner, hidden Self, God, teacher, lineage, vow, conduct, Prajnaparamita, or embodied responsiveness. Their interaction may predict verification architecture, teaching strategy, and reentry more precisely than doctrinal content, boundary operation alone, or custody alone.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold.md:56:- Code at least eight tradition-stage cases, including Advaita, Heart Sutra Prajnaparamita, Rinzai koan curriculum, Cloud of Unknowing, Eckhart, Zhuangzi, Dzogchen, and Sufi fana.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold.md:58:- Use pairs that share one axis but differ on the other, such as Advaita and the Cloud, or Heart Sutra and Eckhart, while checking whether the shared-axis claim survives finer coding.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain.md:7:Status: draft
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain.md:11:A tradition's account of how transformation begins should be treated as a threshold grammar under translation strain. The research unit is not simply the first-break mechanism, and not simply the amount of translation strain. It is the paired record: how the tradition narrates entry, what that narration predicts about threshold safeguards and beginner warnings, and what meanings are lost when the entry grammar is compared across traditions. This model becomes theoretically serious only if first-break type improves prediction after anthropology, authority, conversion process, ritual inheritance, and practice ecology are coded separately.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-threshold-grammar-under-translation-strain.md:29:The synthesis may still be too elastic. Entry safeguards often express several variables at once, including teacher authority, institutional risk control, anthropology, and ritual identity. If coding rules are not fixed before interpretation, the model can redescribe almost any beginner warning as evidence for first-break type. Hybrid instability is especially confounded by politics, language, institutions, and transmission history, so it should remain secondary until the cleaner safeguard and warning tests are complete.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics.md:11:A tradition's credit doctrine should be treated as a dependent diagnostic variable, not a master taxonomy. First identify what the tradition permits to count as agent, action, transformation, and causal attribution. Then score translation strain between traditions. Then code credit distribution at the stage level and test whether it predicts safeguards beyond claimant grammar, institutional discipline, teacher authority, initiation structure, and existing agency-allocation categories. Low-strain cases can support taxonomic claims. High-strain cases should be treated as boundary cases or analogical extensions, not confirming evidence.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics.md:54:- Treat Dogen, Shankara, and Dzogchen as boundary cases unless a source-specific claimant grammar shows that credit language is admissible.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-protective-distance.md:7:Status: draft
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-protective-distance.md:21:- Dogen, Bendowa practice-verification unity, summarized at Encyclopedia of Buddhism, https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen. Used as a countercase where distance is treated as a mistaken split inside practice.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-licensed-training-mistake.md:7:Status: draft
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-licensed-training-mistake.md:29:The strongest objection is that calling a teaching a licensed mistake can insult traditions that present the teaching as literal truth. Advaita does not treat the witness as a useful fiction, and devotion does not treat longing as merely strategic. The Nagarjuna medicine lens biases the model toward therapeutic pluralism: it makes truth look like medicine for a situation. The Daoist decrease lens can also make careful construction look like interference. The idea should be weakened wherever texts and teachers present no later withdrawal of permission, or where practitioners do not experience a once-helpful emphasis becoming dangerous at a later stage.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-licensed-training-mistake.md:54:- Build a licensed-mistake rubric with fields for temporary emphasis, target error, withdrawal practice, shadow if retained, verifier, and stage of training.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:7:Status: draft
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric.md:22:- Primary close-reading: Dogen, Bendowa, Kazuaki Tanahashi translation, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/. Dogen says the dharma is abundant in each person yet not actualized without practice, and that practice and realization cannot be recognized as two separate things. This makes the present act a support locus while forbidding future-gaining ownership.
