./runs/20260526-120003-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1292:The envelope idea may be too tidy. Traditions often combine several effort rules at once: causal preparation, non-attainment teaching, teacher testing, grace, and ordinary discipline. It may also smuggle a modern control metaphor into texts whose main concern is devotion, liberation, obedience, or wisdom. The Daoist decrease lens helped reveal over-effort, but it can make careful cultivation look like interference; right effort corrects this by insisting that some states must be deliberately prevented, abandoned, cultivated, and maintained. The model should be rejected where close practice texts show no stable boundary around effort, or where practitioners do not experience effort as theft-prone.
./runs/20260526-120003-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1330:Status: draft
