./reviews/originality/2026-05-28-holding-without-owning-704d17e4307ae461.json:10:    "A method does not finish when it produces an insight; it finishes when the practitioner learns what may be kept without owning it. Some practices confirm the result and retain the method as a continuing way of seeing. Some validate the method for crossing and then require release. Some undermine the very frame that made the result seem possessable, yet remain embodied as training, community, ethics, or supervision. The decisive question is not only whether a method validates or undermines itself, but who or what holds custody after the method can no longer be treated as a private possession. T"
./reviews/originality/2026-05-28-holding-without-owning-704d17e4307ae461.json:20:  "exact_claim": "A method does not finish when it produces an insight; it finishes when the practitioner learns what may be kept without owning it. Some practices confirm the result and retain the method as a continuing way of seeing. Some validate the method for crossing and then require release. Some undermine the very frame that made the result seem possessable, yet remain embodied as training, community, ethics, or supervision. The decisive question is not only whether a method validates or undermines itself, but who or what holds custody after the method can no longer be treated as a private possession. This matters for modern people whose worth depends on performance: even a liberating method can become another credential unless its completion includes a rule for release, embodiment, and re-entry into ordinary responsibility.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-28-holding-without-owning-704d17e4307ae461.json:59:      "Thinking method source: MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, used as disciplined non-attachment to methods: trust a method enough to cross, then test whether grasping it creates distortion."
./docs/research-architecture.md:26:The working public name is Lumenary. The system should produce daily website updates from the strongest recent observations, plus reviewed X drafts. Do not auto-post to social channels until the review queue and credential handling are explicit.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "No-threshold entry: inherited practice and Dogen's practice-realization grammar, especially Bendowa's claim that beginner practice is already original realization and that there is no beginning in practice.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:46:      "expected_observation": "Failed entry cases will show missing or misassigned ledger functions: no trusted authority, weak community holding, unresolved crisis, mismatched language, unsupported memory practice, or forbidden self-claiming in a grammar that rejects self-power.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:59:    "Tannisho Shinran Other Power self power nembutsu not practice good act chapter 8 translation",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:62:    "Dogen Bendowa practice realization beginner practice realization translation",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:116:      "difference": "The candidate adds tradition-specific authority, vow, ritual, grace, and teacher-held capacity, and asks for manual-level safeguards.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:134:    "Use inherited-practice and Dogen-style no-beginning cases as anomaly tests rather than marginal examples.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:164:      "Shinran, Chapter on Practice, Collected Works of Shinran, plus Tannisho, Matheson Trust page, https://shinranworks.com/the-major-expositions/chapter-on-practice/ and https://www.themathesontrust.org/library/tannisho-shin-buddhist-aphorisms"
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-state-ledger-4299246a4ab81e4e.json:167:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit searched conversion theory, religious coping, legitimate peripheral participation, liminality, upaya, transformative learning, religious socialization, Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic model, Shinran, SN 45.8, Dogen, Augustine, and the Council of Orange. It did not sufficiently close-read Kyogyoshinsho beyond the Chapter on Practice, Augustine and Pelagius in full primary-text sequence, Longchenpa or Mahamudra pointing-out manuals, Sufi bayah and fana texts, or original-language terms for entrusting, effort, vow, grace, and capacity. That gap blocks a candidate-discovery claim.",
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-effort-envelope.md:7:Status: draft
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-effort-envelope.md:23:- Dogen, Bendowa and source card notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md, for practice-realization and present-tense enactment as a check on goal-seeking effort.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-effort-envelope.md:30:The envelope idea may be too tidy. Traditions often combine several effort rules at once: causal preparation, non-attainment teaching, teacher testing, grace, and ordinary discipline. It may also smuggle a modern control metaphor into texts whose main concern is devotion, liberation, obedience, or wisdom. The Daoist decrease lens helped reveal over-effort, but it can make careful cultivation look like interference; right effort corrects this by insisting that some states must be deliberately prevented, abandoned, cultivated, and maintained. The model should be rejected where close practice texts show no stable boundary around effort, or where practitioners do not experience effort as theft-prone.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:27:Structural observation: The pair supports only part of the model. Brihadaranyaka 3.7.23 repeatedly places an inner ruler within earth, beings, organs, mind, and knowledge, then identifies this as Self and immortal. SN 22.59 examines form, feeling, perception, fabrications, and consciousness, then rejects each as mine, self, or what I am because each is inconstant and not masterable. Both disturb ordinary identity and boundary-making, but their final authority structure diverges sharply: one licenses an unobjectifiable Self, the other de-authorizes ownership of all aggregates including consciousness.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:38:- Varela Thompson Rosch embodied mind Buddhism enactive self no self
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:45:- Varela, Thompson, and Rosch, The Embodied Mind, MIT Press overview, https://mitpress.mit.edu/9780262529365/the-embodied-mind/: overlap: Close. Enactivism already reframes cognition as world-disclosure through embodied action and was built in dialogue with Buddhist no-self and mindfulness.; difference: The Interface Invariant Model names a smaller audit-ready set of invariants and compares several traditions rather than building one enactive cognitive-science program.; novelty impact: Moderate to high reduction. The world-disclosure move is old, but the Lumenary operationalization may be useful.
