./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.json:177:      "Tannisho sections 1, 6, and 8, translation by Taitetsu Unno, https://nembutsu.cc/buddhism/the-tannisho/tannisho-sections-i-to-x/"
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.json:180:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit searched conversion studies, doctrine-as-grammar theory, religious coping agency styles, sociology of plausibility structures, liminality, situated learning, upaya, Shinran Other Power, Orange grace canons, Dogen practice-realization, religious socialization, and prior Lumenary capacity-ledger audits. It did not fully close-read Augustine against Pelagius, Longchenpa or Mahamudra pointing-out manuals, Sufi bayah and fana texts, Sri Vaishnava prapatti sources, or original-language terms for faith, entrusting, effort, capacity, grace, and agency. That gap blocks a candidate-discovery claim.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.json:181:    "structural_observation": "SN 45.8 parses the path through practitioner-cultivated functions: right view, resolve, speech, action, livelihood, effort, mindfulness, and concentration. The grammar permits the practitioner to perform decisive training functions, though under Buddhist doctrinal constraints. Tannisho shifts decisive efficacy away from self-power and toward entrusting, Other Power, and the Primal Vow, while also warning against claiming disciples or treating nembutsu as self-owned practice or merit. This supports the candidate's entry-claimant link. It also shows the main risk: the same Shinran material supplies entry grammar, claimant prohibition, danger, and verification language at once, so a prediction test can easily become circular."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:4:    "anomaly_candidate": "Inherited religious formation and Dogen-style practice-realization.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:6:    "why_it_breaks_or_strains_model": "In inherited formation, there may be no discrete threshold act, no single first break, and no separate residue policy available to the beginner. In Dogen-style practice-realization, beginning and realization are not cleanly separated, so the entry grammar may be the same as the fruition grammar. These cases force the model to include no-threshold, no-break, continuous-authorization, practice-realization, and analyst-frame-refused values."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:30:      "test_surface": "Split-source coding across Orange and Augustinian grace texts, Tannisho and Shinran letters, Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manuals, and matched Theravada or Confucian cultivation texts.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:64:    "\"Tannisho\" Other Power self power Primal Vow chapter 11",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:65:    "\"Dogen\" Bendowa practice realization shusho itto",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:118:      "difference": "Tannisho is a primary case rather than a generalized comparative instrument.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:121:      "source": "Shinran and Tannisho Other Power sources, https://www.bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf"
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:127:      "source": "Dogen practice-realization and shusho itto, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:154:  "novelty_adjustment": "Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.54. The four-field compression is useful, but most components have strong near-neighbors in prior Lumenary audits, conversion theory, rites-of-passage theory, doctrine-as-grammar, religious problem-solving styles, legitimate peripheral participation, grace theology, Pure Land Other Power, Dogen practice-realization, VCE factor coding, and Meno-style inquiry paradoxes. The remaining contribution is a conditional first-break rule plus a split-source predictive test, not a discovery-level doctrine candidate.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:181:      "Tannisho and Rennyo Ofumi, BDK English Tripitaka, https://www.bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:183:      "Dogen shusho itto source from Soto Zen, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf"
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:186:    "secondary_literature_gap": "The audit checked accessible primary translations, local prior Lumenary audits, and open sources on conversion, liminality, doctrine-as-grammar, religious coping, legitimate peripheral participation, contemplative adverse effects, grace, Other Power, and practice-realization. It did not fully review Rambo's full monograph, Lindbeck's full book, Japanese, Pali, Sanskrit, Tibetan, Latin, or Chinese originals, Shinran scholarship, Dogen scholarship, Sufi bayah and fana sources, Dzogchen pointing-out manuals, or practitioner interviews.",
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:187:    "structural_observation": "Orange is a near-exact high-severity case: prayer, will, desire, assent, and the beginning of faith are attributed to grace, not unaided nature. Tannisho supplies a vow-held analogue, where entrusting to Amida's Primal Vow displaces self-power and reshapes warning language. SN 22.59 does not fit the same entry grammar, because it negates ownership of aggregates and moves through disenchantment and release without clearly requiring an external break mechanism. Dogen is the strongest anomaly: practice and realization are treated as one, and beginner practice is already implicated in realization, so entry and fruition cannot be cleanly sequenced as threshold and later attainment."
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.json:196:  "unlike_statement": "Unlike Rambo, Lofland-Stark, Van Gennep, Turner, Lindbeck, Pargament, Lave and Wenger, Orange, Shinran, Dogen, VCE, Meno-style inquiry paradoxes, and prior Lumenary entry-residue records, this idea says entry should be coded through four interacting fields, incapacity, minimum participation, break mechanism, and residue policy, and that first-break type becomes irreducible only where a tradition denies that ordinary self-generated threshold entry can found the path."
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-grammar-after-negation.md:7:Status: draft
./observations/codex/2026-05-25-remainder-grammar-after-negation.md:11:When a practice removes the ordinary self, the sharpest cross-tradition difference may be the grammar each system allows after negation. Advaita lets the remainder speak like a noun, the unobjectifiable knower. Early Buddhism treats the candidate self as a predicate failure across the aggregates. Madhyamaka turns the remainder into a self-canceling rule against fixed views. Daoism makes it an adverbial manner, action without forcing. Dogen makes it a tense, the complete present act. Ibn Arabi makes it an address, the world as divine disclosure. The comparison unit is not only what remains, but what grammatical role the remainder is permitted to play.
