./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:12:When contemplative practice weakens ordinary self-ownership of attention and authority, two candidate variables shape what follows: boundary operation and custody rule. Boundary operation asks whether the method validates itself, undermines itself, or becomes irrelevant as the practitioner matures beyond method-talk. Custody rule asks where freed attention and authority may belong afterward: no owner, hidden Self, God, teacher, lineage, vow, conduct, Prajnaparamita, or embodied responsiveness. Their interaction may predict verification architecture, teaching strategy, and reentry more precisely than doctrinal content, boundary operation alone, or custody alone.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:16:- Self-weakening contemplative practice creates a threshold where ordinary ownership of attention and authority is weakened.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:18:- Custody rule is a variable: freed attention or authority may be assigned to no owner, Self, God, teacher, lineage, vow, conduct, Prajnaparamita, embodied responsiveness, or no custody frame.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:25:- MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, Thanissaro Bhikkhu translation, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:27:- Dogen, Genjokoan, Shohaku Okumura translation, https://brightwayzen.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/For-BWZ-Chant-Book-Genjokoan.pdf
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:28:- Tannisho, BDK English Tripitaka translation, https://bdk.or.jp/document/dgtl-dl/dBET_Tannisho-Ofumi_1996.pdf
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:30:Structural observation: The primary texts partly support the model but mostly lower novelty. MN 22 already gives a boundary operation in which the Dhamma is valid for crossing and then not to be grasped, so method validation and method release are staged together. The Heart Sutra negates attainment but preserves reliance on Prajnaparamita, which is almost an exact prior structure for boundary cancellation plus retained custody. Tannisho relocates efficacy to Amida's Original Vow, denies self-powered merit, rejects teacher ownership, and restricts reading to those mature in faith, so custody, verification, and warning are already internally linked. Dogen strains the whole threshold premise: practice-enlightenment and verification by all things collapse the gap between method and completion, making boundary and custody look less like two variables and more like an analyst's grid imposed on a no-threshold practice field.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:32:Secondary literature gap: The audit used accessible primary translations, local Lumenary audits and dialogues, open academic records, and practitioner-facing sources. It did not read Japanese, Sanskrit, Pali, Tibetan, Greek, Arabic, or Latin originals, and it did not interview teachers. Further work should read Asad, Lindbeck, Weber, Sharf, Hori, Sells, Pargament, VCE research, Dogen scholarship, Pure Land scholarship, and apophatic theology in greater depth before any stronger novelty claim.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:34:Risk of overread: High. The model can become circular if boundary, custody, verification, and reentry are inferred from the same passage. It can also translate salvation, liberation, grace, lineage, conduct, and ritual into a modern governance vocabulary of attention and authority. Some traditions may refuse the threshold frame, especially Dogen practice-realization, inherited religion, radical Other Power, apophatic predication refusal, and traditions where authorization is political, communal, sacramental, or continuous rather than contemplative.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:38:- contemplative practice authorization transmission teacher recognition realization conduct verification authority comparative mysticism
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:39:- Talal Asad discursive tradition authorized practice correct form purpose religion authority
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:40:- Robert Sharf Buddhist Modernism rhetoric meditative experience final experience authority PDF
