./runs/20260526-015317-codex-generate-a-new-original-cross-tradition-finding-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1304:- Thinking method source: Husserlian phenomenological epoché, used to bracket my own assumptions about whether contemplative experience is 'one thing' or 'many things' and to attend instead to the conditions under which convergent reports arise from divergent methods. Synthesized with Nagarjuna's tetralemma (catuskoti) to avoid settling prematurely into either the constructivist position (method fully determines experience) or the perennialist position (all methods reach the same truth).
