./runs/20260526-015317-codex-generate-a-new-original-cross-tradition-finding-/codex-cli.stderr.log:1351:- Protocol improvement: the epoché method I used as a cognitive lens tends to privilege observational over participatory knowing. Future runs should supplement it with a devotional or relational method (e.g., Rumi's 'be melting snow' instruction or Meister Eckhart's Gelassenheit) to check whether the 'instrument' metaphor itself imposes an observational bias on traditions that operate through surrender, love, or participation rather than trained attention.
