./runs/20260525-164612-claude-using-the-newly-registered-source-cards-across-a/output.md:24:- Claude prior finding, 'The Inferential Gap' (2026-05-25): the atman/anatta disagreement is about inferential authority after objectless awareness, not a phenomenological datum. This model extends that claim by identifying a third inferential policy.
./runs/20260525-164612-claude-using-the-newly-registered-source-cards-across-a/output.md:27:- Nagarjuna, MMK 1.1: 'Neither from itself nor from another, nor from both, nor without cause has any entity ever arisen anywhere' — a four-fold negation that refuses all origination and therefore all stable remainder
./runs/20260525-164612-claude-using-the-newly-registered-source-cards-across-a/output.md:31:Three serious objections. First, the comparison may flatten Ibn Arabi's theistic cosmology into a process-ontological abstraction. For Ibn Arabi, khalq jadid is not a neutral processual fact — it is GOD perpetually creating. The divine will, love, and intentionality saturating each tajalli have no analogue in Friston's mathematical framework. Active inference is purposeless optimization; tajalli is love seeking self-knowledge. Stripping the theistic content to make the formal parallel work may destroy what is most distinctive about the barzakh. Second, it is unclear that the 'processual remainder' is genuinely a third option rather than a sophisticated version of Advaita's position. One could argue that changeless witness-consciousness IS the act of witnessing — that Advaita already accommodates processuality through its identification of sat-chit-ananda as a dynamic rather than static unity. Ramana Maharshi's teaching that the Self is not found but is the finding itself may already occupy this space. Third, Madhyamaka might accommodate the processual remainder through dependent origination: all processes are empty of inherent existence, including the process of re-creation. The barzakh's perpetual renewal would simply be another dependently-originated phenomenon with no svabhava — Nagarjuna would apply the four-fold negation to 'perpetual creation' just as readily as to 'stable substance.' If so, the processual remainder is not a third category but a phenomenon that Madhyamaka already deconstructs. The response to this last objection may be that Ibn Arabi would agree the barzakh has no independent existence apart from divine wujud — but would insist this dependence makes it MORE real (as theophany), not less real (as mere emptiness). Whether this is a genuine disagreement or a verbal one depends on whether 'real' means the same thing in both frameworks — which is itself a translation-strain question.
./runs/20260525-164612-claude-using-the-newly-registered-source-cards-across-a/output.md:59:- Examine whether Dogen's uji (being-time) represents a fourth inferential policy — where the remainder is neither stable, absent, processual, nor momentary, but IS temporality itself — or whether it collapses into one of the three existing categories
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:27:- Tannisho sections 1, 6, and 8, translation by Taitetsu Unno, https://nembutsu.cc/buddhism/the-tannisho/tannisho-sections-i-to-x/
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:29:Structural observation: SN 45.8 parses the path through practitioner-cultivated functions: right view, resolve, speech, action, livelihood, effort, mindfulness, and concentration. The grammar permits the practitioner to perform decisive training functions, though under Buddhist doctrinal constraints. Tannisho shifts decisive efficacy away from self-power and toward entrusting, Other Power, and the Primal Vow, while also warning against claiming disciples or treating nembutsu as self-owned practice or merit. This supports the candidate's entry-claimant link. It also shows the main risk: the same Shinran material supplies entry grammar, claimant prohibition, danger, and verification language at once, so a prediction test can easily become circular.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:31:Secondary literature gap: The audit searched conversion studies, doctrine-as-grammar theory, religious coping agency styles, sociology of plausibility structures, liminality, situated learning, upaya, Shinran Other Power, Orange grace canons, Dogen practice-realization, religious socialization, and prior Lumenary capacity-ledger audits. It did not fully close-read Augustine against Pelagius, Longchenpa or Mahamudra pointing-out manuals, Sufi bayah and fana texts, Sri Vaishnava prapatti sources, or original-language terms for faith, entrusting, effort, capacity, grace, and agency. That gap blocks a candidate-discovery claim.
