./runs/20260526-140006-codex-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/codex-cli.stderr.log:801:reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-interface-invariant-model-69b3d2b75477d3fe.md:45:- Varela, Thompson, and Rosch, The Embodied Mind, MIT Press overview, https://mitpress.mit.edu/9780262529365/the-embodied-mind/: overlap: Close. Enactivism already reframes cognition as world-disclosure through embodied action and was built in dialogue with Buddhist no-self and mindfulness.; difference: The Interface Invariant Model names a smaller audit-ready set of invariants and compares several traditions rather than building one enactive cognitive-science program.; novelty impact: Moderate to high reduction. The world-disclosure move is old, but the Lumenary operationalization may be useful.
