./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:27:Frontier: What a method does with its own authority
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:32:When a contemplative practice reaches its own threshold, it faces a structural question that may matter more than what it finds: can the method grant itself authority over its own result? Three patterns emerge across independent traditions. In the first, the method confirms itself. The Mandukya Upanishad analyzes waking, dreaming, and deep sleep, then identifies what persists through all three: turiya, 'invisible, beyond practical dealings, beyond...
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:35:- Joshua William Smith, Snakes and Ladders: Therapy as Liberation in Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein's Tractatus, Sophia 2021, https://ueaeprints.uea.ac.uk/id/eprint/80007/: overlap: Very close to the self-canceling core: Nagarjuna and Wittgenstein are read as shared philosophical method without theses, aimed at dissolution of philosophical problems and...; difference: Bilateral comparison only. It does not add self-confirming and self-dissolving alternatives or predict verification architecture across traditions.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:36:- Michael A. Sells, Mystical Languages of Unsaying, University of Chicago Press, https://press.uchicago.edu/ucp/books/book/chicago/M/bo3635525.html: overlap: Apophatic discourse is described as repeatedly turning back upon its own propositions and names, across Greek, Christian, and Islamic texts including Eckhart and Ibn Arabi.; difference: Sells studies apophatic language as discourse, not a general typology of contemplative method completion.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:37:- MN 22 Alagaddupama Sutta, raft simile, Thanissaro translation, https://www.dhammatalks.org/suttas/MN/MN22.html: overlap: The Dhamma is a raft for crossing, to be grasped properly and then let go. This is a direct prior structure for validated-then-abandoned method.; difference: It is not simply canceling or dissolving. It validates proper use, then releases attachment after the crossing.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:40:- Validated-then-abandoned hybrids, especially MN 22's raft, Heart Sutra reliance on Prajnaparamita after no-attainment, and Rinzai koan curriculum after kensho.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:41:- Dogen practice-realization identity, radical Other Power in Tannisho, inherited communal religion, and apophatic refusal in Dionysius.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:47:Rebuild the model as two axes: validates versus undermines, and retained versus abandoned or embodied.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:50:- If: Method-type should predict verification architecture better than tradition membership. Then: Eckhart and Nagarjuna should share more indirect, anti-possessive verification patterns with each other than Eckhart shares with more kataphatic Christian...
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:52:- If: Hybrid traditions should show explicit boundary management between method stages. Then: Texts should mark when to use, trust, undermine, release, or embody a method. Examples would include raft language, preliminary versus main practice, koan...
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:53:- At completion, can the method still authorize its result, or must it be released, denied, or embodied?
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:91:Lumenary should become a public website with daily updates. The research loop should generate original ideas, the publication loop should select the strongest daily findings, and the social loop should draft X posts for human review. Teachings and practices should be written for the modern person, with a named human problem, target cohort, non-fit case, source basis, and observable test.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:268:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:366:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:370:After de-identification, traditions face a practical question: if the ordinary self is no longer trusted as owner, what holds action, care, and meaning together? The answer is a custody policy. Advaita gives custody to unobjectifiable knowing, early Buddhism refuses custody and lets dependent functioning remain ownerless, Zhuangzi gives custody to empty responsiveness, Dogen gives it to the complete present act, Ibn Arabi gives it to divine self-disclosure, and Plotinus gives it to return toward the One. This variable may explain why similar self-emptying practices yield different ethics and metaphysics without treating their resemblance as proof of one hidden reality.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:383:- Additional source cards: Dogen's Uji, Zhuangzi Inner Chapters, Ibn Arabi's Fusus al-Hikam, Plotinus Enneads, and Friston FEP for empirical-adjacent boundary language.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:425:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:507:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:511:When a practice removes the ordinary self, the sharpest cross-tradition difference may be the grammar each system allows after negation. Advaita lets the remainder speak like a noun, the unobjectifiable knower. Early Buddhism treats the candidate self as a predicate failure across the aggregates. Madhyamaka turns the remainder into a self-canceling rule against fixed views. Daoism makes it an adverbial manner, action without forcing. Dogen makes it a tense, the complete present act. Ibn Arabi makes it an address, the world as divine disclosure. The comparison unit is not only what remains, but what grammatical role the remainder is permitted to play.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:568:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:682:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:785:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:890:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:950:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1066:The model may over-psychologize traditions that make explicit ontological claims. It is also currently source-light: it needs direct textual comparison across Advaita, Buddhist, Daoist, Sufi, and Neoplatonic material before it can be promoted beyond draft.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1102:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1202:Transformative practices should first be read through the practitioner's starting agency profile, then through staged handoff events in which capacities are confirmed, ownership is canceled, support is entrusted, or the claimant frame dissolves. The sequence matters: it should predict the practice's warnings, safeguards, repair practices, and non-fit cases. For over-claiming strivers, a practice may need to cancel ownership of a real capacity. For under-claiming people, especially those shaped by coercion, trauma, or denied authority, the first ethical move may be to confirm perception, rebuild boundaries, and permit agency before any surrender or dissolution language is introduced.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1206:The proponent supplied a three-operation vocabulary, but located it too strongly at completion. The challenger supplied a staged handoff rubric, but did not fully develop cohort-gated agency calibration as the prior safety condition. The dialogue produced a candidate synthesis that treats authority transfer as one part of a broader agency-calibration grammar, with predictive and therapeutic constraints. This still needs an originality audit before any promotion.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1269:Some beginnings fail because motivation, trust, attention, judgment, hope, or belonging has been damaged by the very condition a person needs to transform. In those cases, the first useful support is not an authority that replaces agency, but a condition, person, group, treatment, ritual, or practice that temporarily carries missing capacity while returning agency as soon as possible. Traditions narrate this beginning through different grammars such as grace, good friendship, recognition, cultivation, or gift, but comparison should treat those grammars as translation strain until an observable role survives. The practical test is whether the support helps the person begin safely without increasing dependency, coercion, premature certainty, or surrender to an untested authority.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1287:The synthesis may rename existing clinical and recovery wisdom rather than add a new model. It risks becoming too broad because therapy, medication, sponsor, teacher, group, and ritual are not interchangeable. It also risks spiritualizing acute clinical crises where professional care is required. The comparative side still needs blinded coding, since entry warnings may be caused by authority, secrecy, institutional boundary maintenance, or status risk rather than by first-break theory.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1321:- Run the blinded comparative coding study with first-break type, anthropology, institution, authority, ritual inheritance, readiness ecology, and entry-risk governance coded separately.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1332:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1336:At the edge of contemplative practice, the decisive unit is not first a doctrine, a method type, or a final experience. It is a native authority-boundary: the tradition's own way of deciding who is mature, what evidence counts, who may teach, what must be released, and how realization returns to ordinary conduct. Reflexive operations such as confirmation, cancellation, dissolution, and identity should be coded only after this boundary is established from native sources. If those operations then predict authorization, transmission, teaching strategy, and ethical re-entry better than tradition-membership or metaphysical content, they become a real comparative variable. If not, they remain a useful descriptive vocabulary inside a broader authority ecology.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1340:The synthesis is not contained in either source idea alone. The proponent supplied method reckoning, but initially treated completion as the comparable unit. The challenger supplied translation strain, but did not yet produce an authority-boundary model. The dialogue creates a new procedure: audit the native authorization unit first, then test whether reflexive operations explain institutional form. This shifts comparison from final claims to the social and ethical technology that governs maturity.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1347:- Claude rebuttal in turn 2, which revised the model into reflexive operations at the verification boundary and added Dogen's practice-realization identity.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1348:- Codex counter-rebuttal in turn 3, which made native authorization boundaries prior to any clustering analysis and proposed an authority ecology distributed across text, teacher, conduct, community recognition, doctrine, and safeguards.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1354:The candidate may still impose comparability on traditions that do not recognize a discrete arrival, authorization event, or stable boundary. It risks circular coding if the same texts define both the authority boundary and the reflexive operation assigned to it. It also remains vulnerable to textual elitism unless checked against teacher protocols, practitioner reports, community safeguards, and historical institutions. It should not be promoted until an originality audit searches for prior models in comparative mysticism, ritual authority, religious institutional theory, and practice-realization scholarship.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1379:- Run an originality audit on authority-boundary ecology before treating it as new.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1381:- Apply the template to at least eight cases, including Mandukya Advaita, Heart Sutra Madhyamaka, Rinzai koan training, Dogen's Soto Zen, Eckhart, Teresa of Avila, Dzogchen, and Sufi fana.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1397:When contemplative practice weakens ordinary self-ownership of attention and authority, two candidate variables shape what follows: the boundary operation and the custody rule. Boundary operation asks whether the method validates itself, undermines itself, or becomes irrelevant as the practitioner matures beyond method-talk. Custody rule asks where freed attention and authority may belong afterward: no owner, hidden Self, God, teacher, lineage, vow, conduct, Prajnaparamita, or embodied responsiveness. Their interaction may predict verification architecture, teaching strategy, and reentry more precisely than doctrinal content, boundary operation alone, or custody alone.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1442:- Code at least eight tradition-stage cases, including Advaita, Heart Sutra Prajnaparamita, Rinzai koan curriculum, Cloud of Unknowing, Eckhart, Zhuangzi, Dzogchen, and Sufi fana.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1444:- Use pairs that share one axis but differ on the other, such as Advaita and the Cloud, or Heart Sutra and Eckhart, while checking whether the shared-axis claim survives finer coding.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1459:A tradition's credit doctrine should be treated as a dependent diagnostic variable, not a master taxonomy. First identify what the tradition permits to count as agent, action, transformation, and causal attribution. Then score translation strain between traditions. Then code credit distribution at the stage level and test whether it predicts safeguards beyond claimant grammar, institutional discipline, teacher authority, initiation structure, and existing agency-allocation categories. Low-strain cases can support taxonomic claims. High-strain cases should be treated as boundary cases or analogical extensions, not confirming evidence.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1502:- Treat Dogen, Shankara, and Dzogchen as boundary cases unless a source-specific claimant grammar shows that credit language is admissible.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1513:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1572:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1580:The source ideas separately named minimum self and residue policy. The dialogue produced a wider model that asks how receptivity, distributed continuity, authorized remainder, and practice ecology interact. Its possible novelty is not the claim that traditions differ about selfhood, but the testable causal question: whether what a path negates predicts where it stores continuity better than rival variables such as ritual form, institutional dependence, teacher authority, or devotional affect.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1589:- Shared textual pressure: SN 22.59, Chandogya Upanishad 6.8.7 through 6.16, Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23, Dogen's Bendowa, Shinran's Tannisho and Kyogyoshinsho.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1656:The synthesis may still be too elastic. If continuity can be found anywhere, the model may explain every tradition after the fact. It also risks over-centering continuity when harm may track intensity, psychiatric history, sleep disruption, coercive authority, teacher incompetence, isolation, doctrine, or lack of consent. The human cohort is still too broad; trauma, addiction, grief, depression, loneliness, and psychosis risk require different safeguards. Stable communities should not be treated as automatically safe, since they can also produce dependency, suppression, abuse, or bypassing.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1689:- Compare continuity-location predictions against rival variables: practice intensity, duration, teacher contact, community support, psychiatric history, isolation, sleep disruption, authority structure, and consent.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1700:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1704:A contemplative path that weakens ordinary self-ownership needs a custody architecture and a local human interface. Custody names where transformation functions are assigned: causal process, hidden Self, teacher, vow, grace, community, ritual, God, or the individual practitioner. Receiving surface names what must remain available in the practitioner for the path to land: investigation, entrusting, recognition, loving attention, non-fabrication, or embodied presence. The model is not yet entitled to say these are two independent causes. Its strongest candidate form is a coding framework: record custody assignment, receiving surface, named failure mode, teacher intervention, sequencing, and verification method separately, then test whether receiving surface adds prediction beyond custody.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1751:- Define bounded receiving-surface categories before further synthesis: investigating, entrusting, recognizing, waiting, loving attention, non-fabricating, embodied presence.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1765:A self-dissolving or self-transcending path does not merely require a minimum self. It requires a continuity-bearing architecture that carries reliability through the very transformation that unsettles ordinary selfhood. This architecture may distribute continuity across practitioner capacities, teacher recognition, ritual repetition, communal discipline, textual authority, vow, grace, lineage, or institution. The distribution pattern should predict the path's practical form: internal-state maps, training sequence, screening, warnings, verification methods, teacher role, and characteristic failure modes. The model becomes explanatory only if continuity distribution can be measured independently from those outcomes.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1783:The synthesis may be an elegant taxonomy rather than an explanatory theory. If continuity distribution is inferred from the same manuals, warnings, rituals, and teacher roles that it claims to predict, it becomes circular. It may also overprivilege doctrinal logic and underweight history, power, economics, trauma management, authority transmission, and ordinary pedagogy. Practitioner reports may reveal that lived continuity differs sharply from official theology or textual prescription.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1811:- Add controls for institutional age, monastic or lay setting, ritual density, geography, textual versus oral transmission, teacher authority, and known risk-management concerns.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1822:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1885:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:1946:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2009:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2017:Many models ask whether practice begins through effort, grace, insight, social support, or teacher authority. This finding separates those questions. Ordinary supports may get a person through the door, while the path decides what the beginning means and which claims of ownership must be corrected. The possible contribution is a cleaner way to study how teachers guide beginners: not only what brought the person in, but what the path allows the beginner to claim.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2068:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2072:Contemplative traditions install direction through layered mechanisms. Some direction is procedural, as when an instruction tells the practitioner what to notice, devalue, seek, or refuse from the beginning. Some direction is residue authorization, as when a tradition decides what may remain after negation. Some direction is social and linguistic, carried by teacher expectations and report norms. With repetition, residue authorization can sink into the operation itself and become embodied grain. Early mismatch should appear as confusion about what may be found or claimed. Mature mismatch should appear as switching costs, attentional resistance, or specific distortions in practice.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2082:- Dialogue turn 2: residue policy may become embodied grain through repeated practice under doctrinal and pedagogical framing.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2083:- Dialogue turn 3: direction can enter at procedural, interpretive, social, and embodied layers, and grain needs independent markers.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2090:The synthesis risks becoming too flexible. If every similarity can be called convergence, every difference can be called grain, and every doctrinal statement can be called policy in transition, the model loses discriminating force. It needs pre-registered markers, temporal thresholds, and evidence from actual practitioners rather than only elite texts. It must also separate embodied attentional change from learned report vocabulary.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2116:- Pre-register markers of embodied grain: attentional target selection, recovery after distraction, affective valence toward arising phenomena, observer stabilization or dissolution, and switching costs between methods.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2120:- Test whether adverse effects differ by stage: early authorization confusion versus mature embodied directional distortion.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2129:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2148:- Vivekachudamani, MN 10, Shinran's Tannisho, Dogen's Bendowa, The Cloud of Unknowing, and the Bahiya Sutta as candidate cases for different sites of direction.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2182:- Apply the layered rubric to Vivekachudamani, MN 10, Tannisho, Bendowa, Dzogchen pointing-out texts, and The Cloud of Unknowing.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2194:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2215:- Shinran, Tannisho
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2278:- Primary and near-neighbor sources cited in the dialogue: SN 22.59, Chandogya Upanishad 6.8.7-6.16, Shinran's Tannisho and Kyogyoshinsho, Engler on being somebody before being nobody, Lindahl et al. on meditation-related challenges.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2329:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2333:Transformative paths begin by placing unstable attention, trust, agency, and interpretation under some form of custody before the practitioner can fully authorize or understand the path. Traditions then give that custody an entry grammar. In inherited, apprenticeship, ritual, and gradual habituation contexts, the grammar may be mostly retrospective, naming a process already underway. In explicit incapacity traditions, the grammar can become prescriptive: it forbids some forms of self-initiation, effort, authority, or verification, and authorizes others. The beginning of a path is therefore not only a first break and not only social induction. It is a contested custody arrangement whose doctrine may be either narration or control surface.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2378:- Build a coding rubric that separates lived induction, entry doctrine, custody arrangement, effort theory, authority structure, verification method, and characteristic warning language.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2390:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2404:- Dogen, Bendowa practice-verification unity, summarized at Encyclopedia of Buddhism, https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen. Used as a countercase where distance is treated as a mistaken split inside practice.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2519:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2536:- Dogen practice-realization materials in notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md and prior local observations. Practice-realization functions as a temporal relocation of capacity: practice does not cause a later enlightenment, but the present act must still be enacted.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2583:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2715:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2776:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2792:- Dogen, Bendowa and source card notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md, for practice-realization and present-tense enactment as a check on goal-seeking effort.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2799:The envelope idea may be too tidy. Traditions often combine several effort rules at once: causal preparation, non-attainment teaching, teacher testing, grace, and ordinary discipline. It may also smuggle a modern control metaphor into texts whose main concern is devotion, liberation, obedience, or wisdom. The Daoist decrease lens helped reveal over-effort, but it can make careful cultivation look like interference; right effort corrects this by insisting that some states must be deliberately prevented, abandoned, cultivated, and maintained. The model should be rejected where close practice texts show no stable boundary around effort, or where practitioners do not experience effort as theft-prone.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2837:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2900:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2914:- Codex's Entry Ecology challenge: actual beginnings involve context, crisis, trust, inherited practice, authority, language, community, and residual capacity.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2961:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:2976:- Primary close-reading: Dogen, Bendowa, Kazuaki Tanahashi translation, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/. Dogen says the dharma is abundant in each person yet not actualized without practice, and that practice and realization cannot be recognized as two separate things. This makes the present act a support locus while forbidding future-gaining ownership.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3024:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3028:What should we trust after a silence we cannot describe? The first report after an objectless state is not neutral memory; it is a small grammar that assigns authority. One path hears 'I knew nothing' and gives weight to the knowing subject. Another hears 'nothing was felt' and gives weight to the absence of graspable experience. A Daoist text can hear forgetting as successful because body, perception, and cleverness have been left behind. A Sufi practice of remembrance can end by removing the rememberer and giving weight to the Remembered. The comparison suggests a post-gap admissibility rule: after a state that cannot be inspected while it happens, traditions diverge by deciding which part of the later report counts as evidence, the subject, the absence, the transition, the aftereffect, or the relation. The dispute begins when memory is cross-examined.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3032:Near-neighbors already exist: Advaita debates over 'I slept well', Buddhist accounts of cessation, micro-phenomenology of objectless sleep, and pure-consciousness arguments all discuss memory and report. The sharper contribution is not to ask whether memory proves awareness, but to compare how traditions distribute evidential weight across the clauses of post-gap reports. Recollection becomes a trained admissibility practice, not a generic psychological faculty. That gives a practical rubric for comparison without assuming that one report-type carries the same authority everywhere.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3086:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3098:- Thinking method source: Dogen, Bendowa, practice and verification as one, summarized in Encyclopedia of Buddhism: https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3109:The model can romanticize distance and make real suffering, ignorance, or alienation look useful. A Buddhist gradual path may say distance is not a noble instrument but a condition to end through training. A Zen enactment path may say treating no-distance as a function already misses practice-realization. A Sufi may say longing is not a psychological tool but the trace of a real Beloved. The Dogen lens used here may bias the comparison against causal paths by making sequence look like delusion; the mindfulness lens may over-neutralize devotion by turning longing into an observed state. The idea should be weakened unless close practice texts show that each path deliberately trains with its distance policy.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3218:Status: draft
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3231:- Primary close-reading: SN 45.8, https://suttacentral.net/sn45.8/en/bodhi, against Tannisho and Shinran's Notes on Once-Calling and Many-Calling, https://jodoshinshu.faith/tannisho-a-record-in-lament-of-divergences/ and https://shinranworks.com/commentaries/notes-on-once-calling-and-many-calling/. SN 45.8 assigns desire, effort, energy, mind-application, and striving to the practitioner. Shinran's texts make saying and entrusting human-facing while removing calculation from the practitioner's side. The comparison reveals a stage and claimant difference, not merely more or less effort.
./runs/20260528-160005-claude-generate-an-original-lumenary-doctrine-building-/prompt.md:3233:- Dogen practice-realization source: St Andrews Encyclopaedia of Theology on Dogen, https://www.saet.ac.uk/Buddhism/Dogen. Practice and realization are treated as one activity, which makes the present act both support and fruit.
